## 🔹 Prompt 1 — Architecture (START HERE)

```text
You are a senior frontend architect.

Build the architecture for a JavaScript SDK called "ConsentFlow".

Purpose:
A lightweight, embeddable consent widget that improves user experience and conversion rates.

Constraints:
- Must work via a single <script> tag
- No framework (vanilla JS only)
- Lightweight (<50kb)
- Must not block page rendering
- Must support multi-language
- Store consent in both cookies and localStorage

Deliver:
1. Folder/file structure
2. SDK design (global object, methods)
3. Event system design (onConsentChange)
4. Consent data structure
5. Performance considerations
```

---

## 🔹 Prompt 2 — Core SDK

```text
Implement the ConsentFlow SDK.

Requirements:
- UMD pattern (usable via script tag)
- Global object: ConsentFlow

Methods:
- init(config)
- acceptAll()
- rejectAll()
- savePreferences(preferences)
- getConsent()

Storage:
- Save in localStorage + cookies
- Include fallback if localStorage not available

UI:
- Simple bottom banner

Deliver:
- Complete JS file
- Example usage
```

---

## 🔹 Prompt 3 — UI (this is where you win users)

```text
Improve the UI of ConsentFlow.

Goals:
- Clean, premium look (Stripe/Apple style)
- Non-intrusive bottom banner
- Smooth animations
- Mobile-first design

Components:
- Accept All button
- Reject All button
- Customize button (opens modal)

Deliver:
- HTML structure
- CSS styling
- Animation logic
```

---

## 🔹 Prompt 4 — Killer Feature (DIFFERENTIATION)

```text
Add category-based consent logic.

Categories:
- necessary (always true)
- analytics
- marketing

Features:
- Block scripts until consent is given
- Allow scripts after consent
- Provide API:
   ConsentFlow.hasConsent("analytics")

Deliver:
- Script blocking mechanism
- Example with Google Analytics
```

---

## 🔹 Prompt 5 — Production Ready

```text
Prepare ConsentFlow for production.

Requirements:
- Minified version
- Error handling
- No global scope pollution
- Performance optimized
- Lazy load UI

Deliver:
- Production-ready JS
- Optimization notes
```

